        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 1:46PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 146 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ponderosa Park, or 30 miles southeast of Denver, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elizabeth, Kiowa, Ponderosa Park and Franktown.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
